            "tooltip_content": "<p><strong>What is it?</strong></p><p>A silver grid is a network of ultra-fine silver threads woven directly into the fabric at precise intervals, forming a continuous grid structure throughout the textile. Unlike silver ion treatments that are applied to the surface of a fabric and degrade with washing, a woven silver grid is a permanent part of the sheet's construction.</p><p><strong>How does it fight acne?</strong></p><p>The silver ions continuously neutralize the bacteria that cause breakouts — Propionibacterium acnes and Staphylococcus aureus — directly on the fabric surface. Your skin rests on a cleaner environment every night without any additional effort.</p>",
            "tooltip_position": "center",
            "bg_color": "#000000",
            "text_color": "#fafafa",
            "accent_color": "#b45309",
            "desc_color": "#9ca3af"
          }
        },
        "micron_finish_pLUDRz": {
          "type": "micron-finish",
          "settings": {
            "tag": "03 — Non-Absorbent of Products",
            "heading": "Essential Oil Preservation",
            "description": "<p>Unlike heavy terry cloth that soaks up your expensive moisturizers and serums, our fibers are designed to dry your skin surface without stripping away its natural essential oils.</p>",
            "card_title": "SURFACE FRICTION COEFFICIENT",
            "bar_1_label": "Cotton",
            "bar_2_label": "Silk",
            "bar_3_label": "HercLeón",
            "chart_footer": "Lower value indicates smoother surface & less skin irritation",
            "reverse_layout": false,
            "tooltip_trigger": "micron",
            "tooltip_content": "<p><strong>What is a micron?</strong></p><p>A micron (micrometer) is one millionth of a meter. At 10 microns, each Jax fiber is roughly 1/10th the diameter of a human hair. This ultra-fine gauge allows the fibers to bend and drape with almost no resistance, producing a surface that feels remarkably smooth against skin.</p><p><strong>Why does it matter for sheets?</strong></p><p>Finer fibers create a denser, smoother weave with less surface friction. This means less irritation, less pilling, and a softer hand-feel that actually improves with use rather than degrading over time like conventional cotton.</p>",
            "bg_color": "#fafafa",
            "text_color": "#000000",
            "accent_color": "#b45309",
            "desc_color": "#9ca3af"
          }
        }
      },
      "block_order": [
        "acne_shield_Hrcm6j",
        "micron_finish_pLUDRz"
      ],
      "name": "Tab Content - Highlights",
      "settings": {
        "tab_id": "beauty"
      }
    },
    "hc_tab_content_highlights_VprjqV": {
      "type": "hc-tab-content-highlights",
      "blocks": {
        "sweat_management_cDYgzL": {
          "type": "sweat-management",
          "settings": {
            "tag": "02 — Active Temperature Regulation",
            "heading": "Advanced Night Sweat Management",
            "description": "<p>Standard sheets trap heat against your skin, which forces your body to sweat in order to cool itself down and ultimately disrupts your sleep. The Jax Sheets address <strong>Phase Changing Materials</strong> embedded in the fabric that absorb excess heat as your body temperature rises, storing it within the material rather than letting it build up against your skin. As your temperature naturally drops through the night, the PCM releases that stored heat back gradually, keeping your thermal environment stable in both directions. By reducing the heat spikes that trigger night sweats in the first place, these sheets help you stay in the ideal thermal zone for uninterrupted rest.</p>",
            "badge_text": "NASA TECH",
            "reverse_layout": false,
            "tooltip_trigger": "Phase Changing Materials",
            "tooltip_content": "<p><strong>What are PCMs?</strong></p><p>Physically, Phase Changing Materials are specialized, plant based waxes contained within millions of microscopic bubbles embedded in the fabric. These micro capsules allow the wax to change from a solid to a liquid and back again to manage heat, all without making the fabric feel wet or heavy. Because they are part of the fiber itself, they provide a physical temperature solution that will not wash out or lose effectiveness over time.</p>",
            "bg_color": "#000000",
            "text_color": "#ffffff",
            "accent_color": "#b45309",
            "desc_color": "#9ca3af"
          }
        }
      },
      "block_order": [
        "sweat_management_cDYgzL"
      ],
      "name": "Tab Content - Highlights",
      "settings": {
        "tab_id": "performance"
      }
    },
